3jb.title: Commutativity
3jb.text:
A commutative function $f$ is a [function_mathematics function] that takes some inputs from a set $X$ and produces an output that does not depend on the ordering of the inputs.

For example, the binary operation $+$ is commutative, because $3 + 4 = 4 + 3.$ The string concatenation function $\operatorname{concat}$ is not commutative, because $\operatorname{concat}(\text{"1"}, \text{"2"})=\text{"12"} \neq \operatorname{concat}(\text{"2"}, \text{"1"})=\text{"21"}$.
